Linux TimeZones Setting
==========
Regret for the time wasted can become a power of good in the time that remains.

â€“ Arthur Brisbane
==============
Question:
During the daily standup, it was pointed out that the timezone across Nautilus Application Servers in Stratos Datacenter doesn't match with that of the local datacenter's timezone, which is Pacific/Gambier.



Correct the mismatch.
=============
step by step guide answer:
login to stapp01:
ssh tony@stapp01
sudo su
 timedatectl
timedatectl set-timezone Pacific/Gambier
timedatectl
now make sure time zone got updated as per question.
now login to stapp02 & stapp03 and perform above steps.
submit & close the task.
